The paper deals with statistical physics methods and inference applied to signal processing and coding theory, specifically to sparse linear estimation problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The use of graphical models and approximate message-passing algorithm also suggests that the paper may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the application of compressed sensing to real-life problems, which suggests that it may belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
